main event: A witness observed six round UFOs with orange lights moving slowly westward in December 1957.
interesting points: The witness initially reported seeing six objects but later indicated only two were visible at one time., The objects were described as round with glowing orange lights., The case handling was criticized due to hasty closure without proper analysis., The report suggests that the observed objects could potentially be the latest types of Soviet equipment., The document indicates a lack of sufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: six round objects with orange lights
witness description: The witness described the objects as glowing and moving silently.
